# webapp ui surfaces

less is always more. but we want elegant and professional (think tesla or apple, as design companies)

customer conversions, and therefore platform performance (quality, funnel, page speed, marketing/sales, features, accessibility, security, and privacy) are a top priority.

we can take bold, futuristic, never before done design and functionality choices as long as they do not compromise our values. we make technology sexy (think tesla roadster or cybertruck) with our UI. we care rigorously about A/B testing and customer segmenting to maximize reach. 

- **primitives:** shared controls live under `webapp/src/ui/primitives/`; change primitives instead of one-off shadows in feature code.
- prefer to use UI elements that are optimized for performance, eCommerce, and conversions. However, not afraid to try unconventional UI elements in an unusual way to see if it looks refreshing or beautiful on the website.

when editing legacy files, remove redundant shadows in the same area if the change already touches that component.
